snippet.textDisplay:
Sorry but the format of this video was just annoying. The entire format felt incredibly forced, especially with that idiot in the background constantly interjecting while clearly reading a script. 
I get it, you want to appeal to young teens, but if you keep presenting content like this, that's all you're going to be left with, because actual adults will find the content too intolerable to sit through. 
I feel the entire LTT brand has gone downhill, simply because it tries way too hard to be something it's not.

snippet.textDisplay: as a Volta user for over 6months it sounds great at first. We have apple, samsung mini and micro devices galore. However the connection pads will eventually fail. Mostly in the modular plugs. But one of 7 cables failed too. I have been forced to go back to multiple cables in every car and our boat. Another issue is the magnetic connection while it works as advertise this leads to disconnects if you move the device around. If you are trying to use the device while charging you have to be very vigilant not hit the cable.
